  "description": [
    "MIAMI TIMES MIAMI FLORIDA PAGE TWO Between The Lines BY DEAN GORDON B HANCOCK FOR ANP Right Is Winning Newell Dwight Hillis a great and prolific writer of yesteryear said in one of his most inspired moments Nothing is so obvi ous as the slowness of mans up ward progress This seems to be especially true of things relating to the determined fight the Ne gro is making for full integration in this country Even with his hands tied be hind him the Negro is standing up to an untoward situation and is fighting magnificently The two great political conventions just closed in Chicago have been great revelations as to the effectiveness of the Negros fight for liberation That fight is not only being won but being rapidly won The most potent problem that confronted the delegates to those conventions was that of civil rights As an issue it would not down It would take a superoptimist to even dream of instantaneous full integration under either the Republican or Democratic ad ministration In years past the Republicans had ample chance to do something about the Negros secondclass citizenship but they did less than nothing The Democrats through the years have"
